Hi- Impact Television has launched on the StarTimes platform Channel 145 from June 1, 2022. According to a statement on Wednesday, the development was in the television’s bid to expand its viewership across the globe and be in every home in Nigeria. The statement quoted the Assistant General Manager, Hi-Impact Studios, Francisca Ovie, as saying that, “the coming on board StarTimes from June will afford every home the opportunity of watching and enjoying high premium quality programmes the station has been churning out since it made a debut four years ago.” Ovie added that StarTimes enjoys a very wide coverage in Nigeria and other African countries, especially on its Digital Terrestrial Television and Hi-Impact TV hopes to benefit from this arrangement beginning form today to mark our four years in existence. Hi-Impact TV hit Nigeria airwaves on June 1, 2018 and has broadcast for 24 hours since then. Hi-Impact Studios was recently granted a radio licence and is set to commence test transmission next month on 102.1FM.